2. CONDITIONAL FORKING RULES (WHEN YOU CAN AND CANNOT FORK)
You are normally NOT allowed to create public forks or clones of this modpack. However, exceptions are granted strictly under the following conditions:

2.1. UNSUPPORTED GAME VERSIONS: If the Author (playgeymer22852) does not support a specific Minecraft version and has no active version for it on Modrinth/GitHub, you ARE permitted to create a fork strictly for that unsupported version.
2.2. PROJECT ABANDONMENT: If the Author completely abandons the project or archives this GitHub repository, you ARE permitted to continue and maintain a fork of the project.
2.3. REVOCATION OF FORK RIGHTS: If the Author (playgeymer22852) later decides to officially release "Ultimate Optimization" for that previously unsupported version, or un-archives the project to resume active development, your right to continue updating your fork is immediately REVOKED. You must cease further public updates to your version upon the Author's request.

3. REQUIREMENTS FOR ALLOWED FORKS
If your fork meets the conditions in Section 2, you MUST comply with the following:
3.1. ATTRIBUTION: You must prominently credit playgeymer22852 as the original author and provide a direct link to the original Ultimate Optimization pages on GitHub/Modrinth.
3.2. NAMING: You cannot name your project "Ultimate Optimization". It must clearly state it is an unofficial fork (e.g., "Community Fork for Unsupported Version").
3.3. NO CHEATS/COMMERCE: Your fork must remain completely free, cheat-free, and follow all rules in Section 1.

